30/06/2010
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- Police on Tuesday (June 29th) announced the arrest of a man wanted in connection with a suspected Russian spy ring busted in the United States. Christopher Metsors, a 54-year-old Canadian, was detained at the airport in Larnaca as he was about to leave for Budapest. He has been released on $20,000 bail, pending extradition. US authorities arrested ten people Monday, suspected of having acted as Russian spies for over a decade. (AFP, CNN, Reuters - 29/06/10)
